Each one has over 30+ years of highly specialized insurance experience enabling them to provide our clients with the most competitive solutions in the marketplace. In 2000, the Kilbride & Harris team recognized that the unique insurance needs of the Medical Industry were not being met by the current marketplace and decided to develop a boutique-style brokerage firm that concentrated on Medical Malpractice, with a strong emphasis on developing a clear understanding of our clients exposures and offering superior coverage for all facets of their business.  Individual Physicians, Hospitals, Nursing Homes, Group Practices, Healthcare Clinics, and Rehabilitation Facilities require an agent with expert knowledge of their field. We focus not only on the professional liability but the property, worker’s compensation, cyber-liability, business interruption and the overall general liability exposures.  This focus, combined with advanced Risk Management Programs and outstanding Claims Services have enabled us to guide our clients through the many challenges in the medical insurance market.  Our niche approach – not a generalist trying to be all things to all clients – has resulted in an extensive client base throughout New England.

Description: A digital infrastructure company
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: DoDots is a digital infrastructure company that provides online and offline companies with technology that enables all web content to be branded, appropriately packaged and distributed. The company's trademarked product is essentially a small package of Internet content that is delivered directly to customers' desktops. Anything that can be delivered on a web page can be delivered in a Dot, including applications and rich media, but unlike a traditional web page, customers no longer need to 'go out' to the web to interact. DoDots technology allows companies to build product awareness, increase customer response and interaction, remove barriers to purchase, and shorten the sales cycle. Delivered directly to the viewer's desktop or other device and displayed persistently, they increase exposure of messages. Dots are inherently 'permissioned,' so people who receive them are effectively pre-screened as receptive prospects. Dots can be designed to take a viewer to other Dots or to specific web pages for additional product and sales information. Because Dots can be configured to include any application, customers can even purchase products or services directly from them.
